{ The only independent try.   6.f4  Nec6  transposes to the main lines of this chapter. }
6... g6
{ Both sides will fianchetto their dark-squared Bishops on the long diagonal. Usually, White should have a slightly better position, but where in the Budapest arent our chances objectively slightly worse?! What we want are PRACTICAL chances to outplay our opponent. }
